AB  - Two experiments with 592 8-25 yr old Ss demonstrated, through the deployments of auditory and visual space, that children were capable of conceptualizing simultaneously in 2 parallel modes of thought and able to make cross-modal matchings. A 3rd experiment with 225 Ss (7-25 yrs old) concluded that as early as age 7, children acquire the conceptual competence necessary to employ phonetically representational musical orthography. Whether the practice of music could benefit from the introduction of such a system and whether phonetic notations might advantageously be presented into the classroom, are introduced as issues for the musician and music educator to resolve. (5 ref) (PsycInfo Database Record (c) 2021 APA, all rights reserved)
